Greece’s Unions Call 24-Hour Strikes for Oct. 5 and Oct 19

-- B y   N a t a l i e   W e e k s
-- 
2011-09-21T13:00:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/greece-s-unions-call-24-hour-strikes-for-oct-5-and-oct-19.html
Greece ’s biggest private and public
sector union groups, GSEE and ADEDY, will hold two 24-hour
strikes next month to oppose government austerity measures,
Athens-based ADEDY’s Chairman Costas Tsikrikas said.  The 24-hour strikes are scheduled for October 5 and October
19, Tsikrikas said. ADEDY is also holding a three-hour walkout
tomorrow to support state-school teachers. Teachers are holding
a 24-hour strike to protest salary cuts, according to a
statement posted on the Teaching Federation of Greece’s website
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Weeks in Athens at 
 nweeks2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
